git generally adds data

 This session contains details on basic Shell commands required to use Git.
Directory Management commands:
mkdir making a directory
rmdir removing a directory
cd changing the directory to another
cd ..
pwd present working directory
ls list of files in current directory
ls –la


File Management commands:
touch for creating a file
rm (single file) removing
rm (multiple files)
cat (view) content of a particular file
vi (edit) 
cp (copy single file)
cp (copy multiple files)
cp (copy file from one directory to other)
vi:
Hit Escape.
Type :wq!
Hit Enter



Add all permission to a directory:

 –R 777 folder name

Vi:
Open the file using the vi or vim command: vi example_file.
Press the "i" key to enter insert mode.
Make your desired changes. ...
Press the escape "ESC" key to exit insert mode.
Type ":w" and press the enter key to save your changes.
Type ":q" and press the enter key to close the file.


echo is used to print on the screen :w
